19/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Central Election Commission confirmed on Monday (December 18th) that all three candidates for prime minister -- Nikola Spiric, Adnan Terzic and Dragan Vrankic -- meet the criteria of the BiH election law and the law regarding conflicts of interest, making them eligible for the post. 
The three nominees also are being vetted by the State Investigation and Protection Agency. 
Security checks have been completed on Terzic and Vrankic, and Spiric's is under way. 
(Dnevni avaz - 19/12/06; Srna, PBS BiH - 18/12/06)
